{"lemma":"جَزَعَ","slug":"جَزَعَ","root":"ج.ز.ع","root_slug":"ج-ز-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ز-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جَزَعَ","root":"جزع","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5702","n5707","n5703","n5708","n5709","n5710"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be sad, to be unhappy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to worry, to be anxious","examples":[{"text":"أَجْزَعُ مِنْ أُسْتَاذِنَا"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be impatient"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/d͡ʒa.za.ʕa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5702","headword_ar":"جَزْعٌ","root":"jzE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaEa","text_ar":"جَزَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cutting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cutting off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also 8.] ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jzaEa lahu jizoEapF mina AlmaAli","text_ar":"جزَعَ لَهُ جِزْعَةً مِنَ المَالِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut off for him a portion of the property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaEa","text_ar":"جَزَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazoEN","text_ar":"جَزْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed the valley to the other side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed the valley"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed across it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crossed it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmafaAzapa","text_ar":"المَفَازَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmawoDiEa","text_ar":"المَوْضِعَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaziEa","text_ar":"جَزِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaEN","text_ar":"جَزَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juzwEN","text_ar":"جُزوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, impatient,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina","text_ar":"مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"عَلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on account of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alh","text_ar":"اله"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaEN","text_ar":"جَزَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaborN","text_ar":"صَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he had not sufficient strength to bear what befell him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and found not patience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he manifested grief and agitation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, affected with grief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, affected with most violent grief, such as prevented him and turned him from that to which he was directing himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his object, and cut him off therefrom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this meaning of cutting off being said by 'Abd-el-Kádir El-Baghdádee to be the primary signification. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","O","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n5707","headword_ar":"جَزْعٌ","root":"jzE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizoEN","text_ar":"جِزْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, K,) but IDrd ascribes the latter to the vulgar, (TA,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"onyx;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called in the present day;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain beads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gems,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarazN","text_ar":"خَرَزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) (Msb,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beads,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gems,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraz","text_ar":"خَرَز"},{"kind":"text","text":", [here rendered by Golius “ Murœna seu concha Veneris, ” though he also gives what I regard as the only correct signification, namely “ onyx, ”])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of El-Yemen"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) [and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of China,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which are whiteness and blackness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and to which eyes are likened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in particular,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by Imra-el-Keys,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the eyes of wild animals,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because their eyes, while they are alive, are black, but when they die, their whiteness appears; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of stone having many colours, brought from El-Yemen and China;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw;) so called because"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interrupted by various colours; its blackness being interrupted by its whiteness and its yellowness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB:) 'Áïsheh's necklace [which she lost on the occasion that subjected her to the accusation of adultery] was of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazoE","text_ar":"جَزْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Dhafári: (TA:) the wearing it in a signet induces anxiety, or disquietude of mind, and grief, and terrifying dreams, and altercation with men; and if the hair of one who experiences difficulty in bringing forth be wound upon it, she brings forth at once: (K: [and Kzw says the like, and more of a similar kind:]) n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazoEapN","text_ar":"جَزْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, * TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizoEapN","text_ar":"جِزْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, * TA.)       -A2-  See also what next follows."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Kr","TA","IB"]},{"entry_id":"n5703","headword_ar":"جزّع","root":"jzE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajoziyEN","text_ar":"تَجْزِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a full-grown unripe date)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became ripe to the extent of two thirds of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the extent of half of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the bottom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became partly ripe:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner one says of a grape. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a watering-trough, or tank,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had but little remaining in it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put a little water"},{"kind":"text","text":"into a skin. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jz~E fulaAnFA","text_ar":"جزّع فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n. as above, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He caused the impatience"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaE","text_ar":"جَزَع"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such a one to cease:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he said to him that which comforted him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consoled him, and which caused his grief and fear to cease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n5708","headword_ar":"جِزْعٌ","root":"jzE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, L, Msb, K,) but AO says that it should be with fet-h, [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazoEN","text_ar":"جَزْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (K) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of bending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoEaTaf","text_ar":"مُنْعَطَف"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, Msb, K, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoHanFY","text_ar":"مُنْحَنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", As, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a valley:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, Msb, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place where it ends:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of"},{"kind":"page_break","n":420},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crossing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a widening part, of the narrow places,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether it produce plants &c. or do not produce them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or it is not so called unless [it be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a part"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having width, and producing trees &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) or it may be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place, in a valley, in which are no trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking a round and wide form:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajozaAEN","text_ar":"اَجْزَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of alighting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abiding, of a people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Elevated land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground, by the side of which is a low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed, part."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bee-hive:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (Ibn- 'Abbád, K.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazoEN","text_ar":"جَزْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O","L","Msb","K","As","IDrd","TA","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n5709","headword_ar":"جَزُعٌ","root":"jzE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n5710","headword_ar":"جَزِعٌ","root":"jzE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAziEN","text_ar":"جَازِعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazuEN","text_ar":"جَزُعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazuwEN","text_ar":"جَزُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juzaAEN","text_ar":"جُزَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) part. ns. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaziEa","text_ar":"جَزِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Impatient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;] (Msb, K;) but the last two have an intensive signification ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very impatient,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much impatience;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (IAar.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K"]}]}}